HEADWORD: cervid
<hw>cervid</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>any member of the family
<fam>Cervidae</fam>, a type of deer distinguished from the
<fam>Bovidae</fam> by the male's having solid deciduous
antlers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> deer.</syn>⟦br⟧
